solution.p:
A solution must satisfy both equations.  We substitute x=\alert{3} and y=\alert{-2} into the equations. 
    \alert{3} = 5(\alert{-2})+13 ? \amp \amp \text{Yes}
         2(\alert{3})+3(\alert{-2})=0 ? \amp \amp \text{Yes}
Yes, (3,-2) is a solution

